        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 16 at 5:36PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 536 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms near
Oak Trail Shores, or 5 miles northwest of Granbury, moving east at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Oak Trail Shores around 540 PM CDT.
Granbury around 545 PM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Tolar, Lake Granbury,
Acton, Stockton Bend, Waples, Tin Top, Horseshoe Bend, Annetta South,
Cresson, and DeCordova.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight CDT for
north central Texas.</instruction>
